pros:
1. Fast growing multiple times in scale since I joined, market share keeps increasing in Korea; 

2. Surrounded by enthusiastic employees who want to grow and make a success;

3. Flexible working time and work from home policy is super welcomed under Covid situation;

4. Stock compensation is rewarding if you join this company early enough and still stay or exercised your stock options after quitting; 

5. A lot of potentials to grow in long-term (if the business globalization strategy works), which in turn means more job opportunities globally to open for current employees who seek for a different culture and geography to transfer.

6. Never lack of problems to solve, only lacking of time to solve them all at once, hence requiring a good sense of ruthless prioritization;

cons:
1. Common sense is a rare thing in this company, followers are way more than creators and builders; 

2. Attrition of matured and tenured employees are a big concern at least in my area of work, hiring bar of new joiners is not as always high especially when the hiring manager is a new joiner his/herself;

3. Lack of attention on employees' career development almost at all levels from packers inside fulfillment center to vice president level, the company is expecting more for new hires to deliver results than coaching and developing employees' long-term skillsets; 

4. Rating of people related function is from the range of below average to non-existence in aspects of hiring and recruiting, performance evaluation, coach and development, as hire manager it is difficult to get adequate number of qualified candidates, some organization manager may arbitrarily decide all levels' employees performance without consulting other managers' opinion, training is very limited to compliance related but very few relevant to what you need to perform your tasks better.
